using destructure in various context
  1. Normal Function
  2. Arrow function

Array Methods
  Slice --> slice the into a sub-array
    arguments
      start --> starting index
      end --> ends the index **end - 1**
    return ---> array
  splice --> alters the original array
    start --> start index for removing means elements from index to last gets removed
              eg: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5].slice(3); --> removes [4, 5] leaves arr as [1,2,3]
    deleteCount --> instead of deleting till end stop the deletion with deletecount
    ...items ---> items to be replaced in the deleted area
  join --> join the elements and produce a result string
    joins the elements with a separator
    eg: [1,2,3].join('-'); --> 1-2-3
  find --> find an element of the array with a condition
  findLast --> find the last element of the array with a condition
  findLastIndex --> find the index of an element of the array with a condition 
  lastIndex --> find the last index of an element of the array with a condition 

